Title: Aloe Veda Herbal Conditioning Shampoo(200 ml)
Description: Pamper your hair with the Aloe Veda Herbal Conditioning Shampoo. This conditioning shampoo is rich in nutrients which make your hair lustrous. This Aloe Veda shampoo is a powerful infusion of herbal ingredients like Oils of Hibiscus, Aloe Vera, Cinnamon Leaf, Henna, Amla, Shikakai, Tulsi, Neem, Bramhi and Bhringraj which combine to revitalize your hair from within. Hibiscus extracts can provide the essential vitamins and minerals required to repair damaged cells and tissues and boost the growth of healthy hair. Henna is a natural conditioner which retains the moisture level of your hair and hydrates your scalp, thereby keeping your hair soft and silky. Shikakai is an effective cleanser which goes into all the layers of your scalp and purges out impurities, in order to keep your hair refreshingly clean at all times. Neem is an extremely beneficial herb which comes with anti-bacterial properties that can prevent dandruff and parasite infection. The antiseptic property of Neem can soothe your scalp and provide relief from burns, scars and irritation. Aloe Vera moisturises and conditions your hair and can prevent dryness. Aloe Vera extracts present in this shampoo can eliminate excess Kerotin on the scalp, thus reducing dandruff. This herbal shampoo can retain the pH balance of your hair, thus adding extra smoothness. The nourishing Aloe Veda shampoo enriches the radiance of your skin while it also makes your skin sweetly perfumed. This conditioning shampoo does not contain any artificial fragrance. Directions for Use Apply on wet hair. Lather well and massage for two minutes. Rinse off. Use regularly for best effects.

Title: Ayurveda Essentials Naturally Healthy Skin - Neem Oil(100 ml)
Description: One of the Sanskrit names for neem, ‘Arishtha’, bears the meaning “reliever of sickness” and is indicative of the reverence inspired by this widely used medicinal plant. In fact, neem is often seen as a promoter of general health. In Ayurveda, neem typically balances excess pitta and kapha. (If you are looking to remove excess pitta and kapha, support your colon and bowel movements with rejuvenating herbs like Triphala.) Neem’s cold, light, and dry qualities tend to aggravate vata. Neem oil has traditionally been applied to the skin as a means of soothing and lubricating the skin, calming irritated and heated sensations, maintaining comfortable body temperature, supporting the skin’s immunity. It is often applied to the hair and scalp to promote luster and overall health, or to the palms of the hands and soles of the feet to support appropriate perspiration in these locations. Neem oil can also be used as a deodorant for malodorous sweat. It is likewise recommended for the maintenance of healthy teeth and gums as well as overall oral hygiene. Further, neem oil also has numerous applications as a deterrent against mosquitoes and other insects. In this capacity, neem oil can help protect individuals from insect bites.
